Branford Castle Partners, L.P.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 2:03 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Branford Castle Partners, L.P.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Branford Castle Partners, L.P. is a private equity firm specializing in growth capital, buyouts, recapitalizations, and industry consolidations in middle market, and mature companies. The firm seeks to invest in both public and private companies. It prefers to invest in small to medium sized old economy businesses. The firm is a generalist but have specific areas of expertise in restaurants, commercial distribution, and services industries. It prefers to invest in the consumer products and services, logistics, value-added commercial distribution, business services, restaurants, industrial, manufacturing, marine products and services, materials, and medical services sectors. The firm prefers ...
Branford Castle Partners, L.P. is a private equity firm specializing in growth capital, buyouts, recapitalizations, and industry consolidations in middle market, and mature companies. The firm seeks to invest in both public and private companies. It prefers to invest in small to medium sized old economy businesses. The firm is a generalist but have specific areas of expertise in restaurants, commercial distribution, and services industries. It prefers to invest in the consumer products and services, logistics, value-added commercial distribution, business services, restaurants, industrial, manufacturing, marine products and services, materials, and medical services sectors. The firm prefers to invest in North America, United States, and Canada based companies. The firm typically invests between $1 million and $40 million in platform or stand-alone businesses with revenues between $10 million and $200 million, essentially under $100 million, enterprise values between $7 million and $75 million, and EBITDA between $1.5 million and $15 million. The average holding period for the firm is more than 10 years. It makes control and non-control investments and seeks to take majority stake and acquire the Board seat in its portfolio companies. The firm uses its own private capital for investments. Branford Castle Partners, L.P. was founded in 1986 and is based in New York, New York.
